content: App is not supporting the android 10(Q). AS i have tried every possible step that can help me out.. bht still nothing happens .. basically the app is getting killed by battery optimization , rather enable or disable , matter remains the same .. Whenever u wanna use the services of the app , first of all u always need to give a restart to the app , to get all the app's forced to worked on 90hz .. I m Sorry Dev's but i think Changing the value to zero is a better option and it is free too .
replyContent:
There were no previous Android 10 specific issue reports, including battery optimizations killing Auto90.

Auto90's purpose is to give users the control on which apps 90 Hz kicks in as using 60 Hz in less-intensive apps can save significant power(100mW). Changing the value permanently to 0 via adb causes significant power drain.
